{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/bndshl","slide":2,"text":"30 seconds\n\nThe system had five main requirements. The UI should not know imported mesh indices. It needed to support both negative-to-positive and zero-to-positive morphs, preserve separate recipes for each character, accept future gameplay inputs as well as sliders, and fail safely when a model is incomplete. Those constraints shaped the architecture more than the raw number of controls."}
