{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/19711n","slide":3,"text":"55 seconds\n\nThere are two input paths. Manual controls arrive through the authored UI prefab. Gameplay muscle and body-fat values arrive through StatGrowthDefinition. Both paths cross the same stable morph-ID boundary and call CharacterMorphController. The controller owns the active character recipes and resolved bindings, then applies positive and negative weights to every matching SkinnedMeshRenderer. CharacterMorphCatalog is the only part that needs to know model-specific FBX shape names. For example, the rest of the system uses body.weight rather than a mesh index or imported shape string."}
