{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/3ylc7u54","slide":4,"name":"oop-thesis","text":"Inheritance removes morph-type decisions from the controller.","textPreview":"Inheritance removes morph-type decisions from the controller.","textChars":61,"textLines":1,"bbox":[710,585,470,40]}
{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/9ubjwa","slide":4,"text":"40 seconds\n\nThe inheritance is domain-specific rather than relying on the fact that Unity components inherit MonoBehaviour. CharacterMorphDefinition is the abstract contract. Bipolar and positive-only definitions inherit the shared metadata and shape-name lookup, then override their range, binding requirements and weight calculation. The controller asks the base type to calculate weights, so it does not need a growing set of type checks. Recipes and renderer bindings also remain private, which protects state from unintended changes."}
