{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/bm58z25k","slide":5,"name":"dependency-footer","text":"Composition keeps the stat source separate from bipolar or positive-only morph behaviour.","textPreview":"Composition keeps the stat source separate from bipolar or positive-only morph behaviour.","textChars":89,"textLines":1,"bbox":[640,570,500,52]}
{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/8jnjk6","slide":5,"text":"40 seconds\n\nDependency management centres on stable meaning. The UI and recipes use body.weight. The catalogue translates that into the imported positive and negative FBX shape names. That isolates model-specific details. Stat growth is composition rather than another morph subclass, because input source and morph behaviour are different responsibilities. The host game owns the progression rules and sends a normalised value. For body fat, zero maps to the slim shape, one-half is neutral, and one maps to the heavy shape."}
