{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/8azi4v","slide":7,"text":"30 seconds\n\nThe strongest result is that responsibility is visible: stable IDs protect the UI and recipes, the controller encapsulates runtime state, concrete definitions own morph behaviour, and the validator protects authored setup. The main trade-offs are the hardcoded MPFB catalogue, in-memory recipes and the current UI scene overrides. My next step would be to return final visuals to the prefab, add tests for stat-growth mapping and move model data into serialised profiles. The broader lesson is to build a reusable boundary first and leave game-specific progression with the host game."}